abstract: Labor Dept reports initial claims for state unemployment benefits rose 6,000 to seasonally adjusted 278,000 for week ended Feb 27; Challenger, Gray & Christmas reports companies based in United States announced 61,599 layoffs in February, down from 75,114 in January; Commerce Dept reports manufactured goods orders rose 1.6 percent in January, from 2.9 percent drop in December.
lead_paragraph: Initial claims for state unemployment benefits increased 6,000 in the week ended Feb. 27.

headline.main: Jobless Claims Rise, but Layoffs Fell Sharply
headline.print_headline: Jobless Claims Up, but Layoffs Fell Sharply in February
